address: 97XM+47H, Gunungsari, Gulon, Salam, Kuncen, Seloboro, Kec. Salam, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56484, Indonesia
name: Endang Irgha
text: Ingin merasakan petualang tracking di Gunung datanglah ke Candi Gunungsari terletak di Gulon Salam Magelang. Jalan ke arah Candi bagus. Namun masuk lokasi harus melewati pemakaman setempat baru naik ke arah Candi. Ada mushola dan tempat parkir luas untuk mobil, bus tidak bisa masuk ke tujuan. Datanglah pada musim kemarau seperti saat ini Minggu 4 Nopember 2018. Karena jalan menanjak masih original hutan bambu dan belum tertata, jalan tanah, banyak pohon yg tumbang, tangga naik masih terbuat dari tanjakan bambu. Gak ada masalah yg penting hati-hati. Memang disetiap tikungan menanjak dibuat tempat istirahat para pendaki. Menuju puncak ada tempat yg sungguh indah untuk melihat Kota Magelang dari atas bukit. Tempat yg sudah disediakan oleh penduduk sekitar semacam dari bambu yg menjorok. View paling indah untuk foto spot, sampai stadion Magelang juga terlihat dari atas. Sungguh menakjubkan. Sambil tiduran menahan kelelahan akhirnya terbayar sudah dg pemandangan yg sangat indah. Setelah puas fotografi baru naik lagi menuju pintu masuk Candi Gunungsari peninggalan Hindu. Ternyata Candi Gunungsari itulah posisi puncak Gunung Gunungsari. Siapkan tenaga dan bawa amunisi karena belum ada warung yg jualan air. Hehhe... Amazing space.. mungkin suatu saat lagi bisa dijadikan tujuan wisata anak cucu kita. Selamat berpetualang jelajah Indonesia tercinta. 😎😍😛
textTranslated: Want to experience adventurous tracking on the mountain, come to Gunungsari Temple located in Gulon Salam, Magelang. The road to the temple is good. However, to enter the location you have to pass through the local cemetery and then go up towards the temple. There is a prayer room and a large parking area for cars, buses cannot enter the destination. Come during the dry season like now, Sunday 4 November 2018. Because the road uphill is still in the original bamboo forest and has not been laid out, the road is dirt, there are lots of fallen trees, the stairs up are still made of bamboo ramps. There's no problem, it's important to be careful. Indeed, at every uphill bend, there is a resting place for climbers. Towards the top there is a really beautiful place to see Magelang City from the top of the hill. The place that has been provided by local residents is a kind of overhanging bamboo. The most beautiful view for photo spots, even the Magelang stadium can be seen from above. So fabulous. While lying down to endure fatigue, it finally paid off with a very beautiful view. Once you are satisfied with photography, then go up again to the entrance to the Hindu Gunungsari Temple. It turns out that Gunungsari Temple is the peak of Mount Gunungsari. Prepare your energy and bring ammunition because there are no stalls selling water. Hehhe... Amazing space.. maybe one day it can be used as a tourist destination for our children and grandchildren. Have a good adventure exploring your beloved Indonesia. 😎😍😛
title: Gunungsari Temple

name: Muhammad Abdi Fattah
text:
Candi Gunung Sari yang terletak di Kecamatan Salam ini menyuguhkan pemandangan yang indah. Apalagi jika kita datang saat pagi maka bisa mendapat pemandangan sunrise dan gagahnya gunung Merapi-Merbabu di kejauhan.

Karena letaknya yang berada di atas bukit mengharuskan kita untuk trekking ke puncak kurang lebih 15-30 menit tergantung kondisi fisik masing-masing orang. Trekking bisa melalui tiga jalur yang sudah tersedia dengan jalur tercepat melalui dusun lengkong dan jalur ternyaman melalui sisi timur bukit yang mana di jalur ini terdapat parkiran cukup luas, gazebo, dan bahkan camping ground. Namun perlu kehati-hatian jika ingin camping di sini karrna masih banyak kera yang menghuni bukit ini.

Kondisi candi memang sudah tidak berbentuk dan hanya bertumpuk-tumpuk namun tertata rapi.
textTranslated:
Gunung Sari Temple, which is located in Salam District, offers beautiful views. Moreover, if we come in the morning we can get views of the sunrise and the majestic Mount Merapi-Merbabu in the distance.

Because it is located on a hill, it requires us to trek to the top in approximately 15-30 minutes depending on each person's physical condition. Trekking can be done via three available routes, with the fastest route through Lengkong hamlet and the most comfortable route via the east side of the hill, where on this route there is a fairly large parking lot, gazebo and even a camping ground. However, you need to be careful if you want to camp here because there are still many monkeys that inhabit this hill.

The condition of the temple is no longer in shape and is just piled up but neatly arranged.
title: Gunungsari Temple

text: Candi Gunung Sari　なんと小高い山の頂上に位置しているヒンズー教遺跡、後で地図から調べたら山の上り始めから標高差は90ｍ。20分くらいで頂上へ行けますが、気合を入れて登らないといけません。。汗だくになります（笑）　しかも途中で疲れて休んでいると今度は蚊の大群が押し寄せてきますから防虫剤を持参しましょう。さて、山の頂上の遺跡に出会うと感動しますと同時に眼下に広がるのどかな街の風景がなかなか良かったですよ。遺跡自体はかなり老旧化が進んでいました。なんとか復元してもらえれば遺跡も喜ぶと思います＠197
textTranslated: Candi Gunung Sari　This is a Hindu ruin located on the top of a small mountain.I later looked it up on a map and found out that the difference in altitude from the start of the climb is 90 meters. You can reach the top in about 20 minutes, but you have to be determined. . You'll be sweating (lol), and if you get tired midway through and take a rest, swarms of mosquitoes will swarm you, so be sure to bring insect repellent. Well, I was moved when I came across the ruins on the top of the mountain, and at the same time, the view of the idyllic city below was quite beautiful. The ruins themselves were quite old. I think the ruins would be happy if they were restored somehow @197

text:
Candi ini terletak di atas bukit. Ada dua jalan untuk mencapai candi ini. Pertama rute melewati pemukiman warga (jalan sudah lumayan enak, melewati pemakaman di bukit). Yang kedua dari pinggir jalan langsung naik ke atas bukit (agak susah jalan melewati rute ini karena alang-alang yang tinggi). Keduanya sama-sama mendaki dan melewati hutan bambu.

Dipertengahan jalan menuju candi terlihat pemandangan Gn. Merapi dan Merbabu.

Menurut penjaga candi, banyak kera/monyet yang tinggal disekitaran bukit. Kebetulan saya hanya mendengar suaranya saja. Jadi jaga barang bawaan ketika berjalan di bukit.
textTranslated:
This temple is located on a hill. There are two roads to reach this temple. The first route passes through residential areas (the road is quite good, passing the cemetery on the hill). The second one is from the side of the road straight up the hill (it's a bit difficult to walk this route because of the high reeds). Both of them climbed and passed through the bamboo forest.

In the middle of the road to the temple you can see the view of Mt. Merapi and Merbabu.

According to the temple guard, many monkeys live around the hill. Coincidentally I only heard his voice. So take care of your belongings when walking on the hill.
title: Gunungsari Temple

textTranslated: Gunung Sari Temple, you can see the ruins of buildings like those from the Hindu Shiva era. There are remains of ruins such as the Yoni phallus which is the character of this temple. Located at the top of a hill with the south side facing the majestic Mount Merapi. Beautiful trees and cool air accompany the path to the temple and occasionally you will find wild monkeys hanging around looking for food. On the lower side there is the burial of the king of Mataram.

Terlepas dari itu semua sebetulnya candi sari ini sudah dikenal masyarakat sekitar gunung sari, karena minimnya infrastruktur dan akses masuk candi menjadikan kurangnya daya tarik wisatawan untuk berkunjung ke candi sari, hal itu sudah teratasi sampai saat ini karena untuk akses masuk candi sudah bisa dilewati kendaraan roda dua bahkan komunitas jeep sudah mencoba treek yang dibangun tokoh masyarakat sekitar candi sari.

Untuk akses masuk candi bisa dari dua arah selatan dan utara, kalau dari selatan bisa melewati treek of road dan bisa singgah di balkondes milik salah satu warga disekitar candi dan gardu pandan, untuk dari yang arah utara sudah nampak bila dari jl jogja magelang.
textTranslated:
Starting from the concern of the GUMILAR youth for caring about nature to build this Sari temple so that it can be preserved and can boost the economy in Seloboro village, the Gunung Sari temple was rebuilt so that it becomes a natural tourist attraction that can be commercialized for the community around Gunung Sari.
Apart from all that, Sari Temple is actually well known to the people around Gunung Sari, because the lack of infrastructure and access to enter the temple has resulted in a lack of attraction for tourists to visit Sari Temple. This has been resolved so far because access to the temple is now possible. passed by two-wheeled vehicles and even the jeep community has tried out the trees built by community leaders around the Sari temple.

Access to enter the temple can be from two directions south and north, if from the south you can pass through the tree of the road and can stop at the balcony of one of the residents around the temple and the pandan substation, from the north it can already be seen from Jl Jogja Magelang .
title: Gunungsari Temple

address: Q332+3X, Pringapus, Ngadirejo, Pringapus, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: Ahmad Dzikri Al Kafi
text:
Salah satu peninggalan sejarah di Kabupaten Temanggung yang unik dan menarik untuk dipelajari adalah Candi Pringapus. Sesuai namanya, candi tersebut terletak di desa Priangapus, Kecamatan Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah.

Daerah situs Candi Pringapus dan sekitamya merupakan wilayah endapan lahar gunung Sindoro yang memiliki karakteristik tanah subur, sehingga sekitarnya digunakan untuk kebun oleh warga setempat.

Keunikan lain dari Candi Pringapus adalah lokasinya yang berada di tengah-tengah perkampungan penduduk dan diapit oleh kebun produktif milik masyarakat.

Dibangun pada 850 Masehi

Sejarawan Universitas Sebelas Maret (UNS) Rendra Agusta menuturkan, Candi Pringapus pertamakali disebut 1844 pada catatan peneliti asal Jerman, Junghuhn yang kala itu sedang melakukan penelitian di Pulau Jawa.

Berdasarkan catatan Junghuhn, adanya candi lain yang berdiri sekitar 300 meter dari Candi Pringapus yang bernama Candi Perot.

"Menurut catatan sejarah dan temuan benda arkeologi disekitarnya, Candii Pringapus memiiki luas 29,68 meter persegi dan dibangun sekitar 850 Masehi dengan dominasi komponen batu andesit," kata Rendra, Sabtu (15/7).

Selain itu, Rendra mengatakan, Candi Pringapus berasal dari zaman pemerintahan Dinasti Syailendra, di masa yang tidak jauh berbeda dengan pembangunan Candi Borobudur dan Candi Prambanan.

Rendra menjelaskan, Candi Pringapus pertamakali direstorasi dan dipugar oleh Dinas Purbakala Pemerintah Kolonial pada 1930.

"Dilihat dari bentuk bangunannya, Candi Pringapus berarsitek Hindu Syiwa dengan struktur bangunan menyerupai Mahameru atau tempat tinggal para dewata," tuturnya.

Hal tersebut terbukti dengan adanya arca Lembu Nandini, kendaraan Syiwa, dan relief hapsara-hapsari yang menggambarkan makhluk setengah dewa.

Menengok lebih dalam ke struktur Candi Pringapus, pengunjung bisa melihat satu buah candi, seperti Candi Bima yang ada di Banjarnegara.

Di sekitar Candi Pringapus dipenuhi rerumputan hijau yang biasanya dimanfaatkan pengunjung untuk duduk-duduk.

Terbuat dari Batu Andesit

Juru Kunci Candi Pringapus, Daryono menuturkan, bangunan bersejarah tersebut tersusun dari bebatuan andesit, yang terdiri dari 3 bagian yakni bawah, tengah dan atas.

"Bawah merupakan kaki candi atau Bhurloka, yang menyimbolkan dunia bawah atau dunia pendosa," kata dia.

Sedangkan bagian tengah, kata Daryono, merupakan badan candi yang disebut Burwaloka, yang menyimbolkan tempat orang-orang suci yang terbebas dari dosa.

"Bagian atas atau Swarloka, yang merupakan simbol alam atas yakni tempat bersemayamnya para dewa," tuturnya.

Daryono menjelaskan, Candi Pringapus mengahadap ke arah barat, dan di dalamnya terdapat arca Nandini yang merupakan sapi tunggangan dari Dewa Syiwa.

"Dalam candi tersebut terdapat arca lembu dalam posisi duduk. Di sebelah barat bangunan candi, di tepi 'sendang' (danau kecil) terdapat sebuah lingga dan arca sapi," ujarnya.

Menurut Daryono, penduduk setempat meyakini, arca sapi ini merupakan penjaga ketersediaan air sendang.

Sebab, salah satu keunikan sendang tersebut adalah airnya tidak pernah kering meskipun pada musim kemarau berkepanjangan.
textTranslated:
One of the historical heritages in Temanggung Regency that is unique and interesting to study is Pringapus Temple. As the name suggests, the temple is located in Priangapus village, Ngadirejo District, Temanggung Regency, Central Java.

The area of ​​the Pringapus Temple site and its surroundings is an area of ​​Mount Sindoro lava deposits which has the characteristics of fertile soil, so the surrounding area is used for gardens by local residents.

Another unique thing about Pringapus Temple is its location in the middle of a residential village and flanked by productive gardens belonging to the community.

Built in 850 AD

Sebelas Maret University (UNS) historian Rendra Agusta said that Pringapus Temple was first mentioned in 1844 in the notes of a German researcher, Junghuhn, who at that time was conducting research on the island of Java.

Based on Junghuhn's notes, there is another temple that stands about 300 meters from Pringapus Temple, called Perot Temple.

"According to historical records and findings of archaeological objects around it, Pringapus Temple has an area of ​​29.68 square meters and was built around 850 AD with the dominance of andesite stone components," said Rendra, Saturday (15/7).

Apart from that, Rendra said, Pringapus Temple originated during the reign of the Syailendra Dynasty, in a period that was not much different from the construction of Borobudur Temple and Prambanan Temple.

Rendra explained that Pringapus Temple was first restored and restored by the Colonial Government Antiquities Service in 1930.

"Judging from the shape of the building, Pringapus Temple has a Shiva Hindu architecture with a building structure resembling Mahameru or the residence of the gods," he said.

This is proven by the existence of the Lembu Nandini statue, Shiva's vehicle, and hapsara-hapsari reliefs depicting semi-god creatures.

Looking deeper into the structure of Pringapus Temple, visitors can see a temple, such as Bima Temple in Banjarnegara.

Around Pringapus Temple is filled with green grass which visitors usually use for sitting.

Made from Andesite Stone

The caretaker of Pringapus Temple, Daryono, said that this historic building is made of andesite rock, which consists of 3 parts, namely lower, middle and upper.

"The bottom is the foot of the temple or Bhurloka, which symbolizes the underworld or the world of sinners," he said.

Meanwhile, the middle part, said Daryono, is the body of the temple called Burwaloka, which symbolizes the place of holy people who are free from sin.

"The upper part or Swarloka, which is a symbol of the upper realm, is where the gods reside," he said.

Daryono explained that Pringapus Temple faces west, and inside there is a statue of Nandini, who is the cow riding by the god Shiva.

"In the temple there is a statue of an ox in a sitting position. To the west of the temple building, on the edge of the 'sendang' (small lake) there is a phallus and a statue of a cow," he said.

According to Daryono, local residents believe that this cow statue is the guardian of the availability of spring water.

Because, one of the unique things about this spring is that the water never dries up even during the prolonged dry season.
title: Pringapus Temple

text: Candi Perot merupakan candi yang sebenarnya candi acuan untuk candi Pringapus, untuk penanggalan nya. Yang kita jumpai sekarang adalah candi Pringapus. Korelasi penanggalan untuk Candi Pringapus ini di dapat dari prasasti yang di temukan di candi Perot. Prasasti Tulang Air 1 dan 2 yang menyebut angka tahun pembangunan candinya yaitu pada hari Minggu Paing tanggal 15 Juni 850 M atau 772 C. Raja yang berkuasa saat itu Rakai Pikatan. Tapi apakah candi ini di resmikan atau mulai dibangun pada masa Rakai Pikatan, belum ada penelitian.  Di tempat ini di jumpai juga arca Durga, antefik yang berelief kala, kemuncak dan yoni. Dari banyak nya kala yang ditemukan diindikasikan bahwa ada beberapa Candi lain di tempat ini. Arca Nandi di tempat ini juga istimewa, indah.
textTranslated: Perot Temple is a temple that is actually a reference temple for Pringapus Temple, for its calendar. What we see now is the Pringapus temple. The dating correlation for Pringapus Temple can be obtained from the inscription found at Perot Temple. The Tulang Air inscriptions 1 and 2 state the year the temple was built, namely Sunday Paing, June 15, 850 AD or 772 C. The king who ruled at that time was Rakai Pikatan. But whether this temple was inaugurated or started to be built during the Rakai Pikatan period, there has been no research.  In this place you can also find a statue of Durga, an antefic with reliefs of kala, kemuncak and yoni. From the many kalas found, it is indicated that there were several other temples in this place. The Nandi statue in this place is also special, beautiful.
title: Pringapus Temple

name: Keperluan Penelitian
text:
Candi Asu Sengi merupakan salah satu dari tiga candi yang berdekatan di pos sengi. Di dekatnya ada Candi Pendem Sengi dan Candi Lumbung Sengi.

Kemungkinan besar merupakan candi Hindu, hanya kaki candi dan setengah badan candi saja yang utuh.

Candi ini mudah untuk diakses karena berada di pinggir jalan raya, diantara perkebunan warga. Waktu ke tempat ini dalam keadaan tutup waktu itu pukul 14:30, sepertinya Candi Asu dan Candi Pendem yang di dekatnya tutup pukul 14:00. Bila ke candi ini diatas jam itu candi masih bisa dikunjungi hanya tidak bisa masuk ke dalam karena pintu pagar terkunci.

Tidak ada fasilitas parkir atau toilet. Tidak ada tiket masuk ke tempat ini. Sepertinya cukup melapor ke petugasnya kalau ingin masuk ke candi.
textTranslated:
Asu Sengi Temple is one of three adjacent temples at the Sengi post. Nearby are Pendem Sengi Temple and Lumbung Sengi Temple.

Most likely a Hindu temple, only the foot of the temple and half of the body of the temple are intact.

This temple is easy to access because it is located on the side of the main road, between residents' plantations. The time this place closed was at 14:30, it seems that Asu Temple and the nearby Pendem Temple closed at 14:00. If you go to this temple after that time, you can still visit the temple, but you can't go inside because the gate is locked.

There are no parking or toilet facilities. There is no entrance ticket to this place. It seems that you just need to report to the staff if you want to enter the temple.
title: Asu Temple

name: galih akademik
text: Akhirnya ketemu 1 lagi bagian komplek candi sengi. Candi Asu Sengi ini terletak di tengah sawah. Jalur jalan desa antara magelang ketep ke arah boyolali lewat jembatan kecil. Candi Asu terletak di Dusun Candipos, Kelurahan Sengi, Kecamatan Dukun, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah. Sayang pagarnya tergembok, jadi gak bisa lihat dalamnya. Penamaan Asu (anjing:jawa) oleh warga lokal karena terdapat arca lembu nandi yg bentuknya mirip asu. Dibangun abad ke-9 masa rakai Kayuwangi Dyah Lokapala dari Kerajaan Mataram Hindu. Berdasarkan Prasasti Sri Manggala II, Kurambitan I dan Kurambitan II disebutkan terdapat Dharma Salingsingan yang dibangun tahun 802 caka.  Mirip dan hampir sejaman dengan candi-candi mataram hindu lain seperti Candi Gedongsongo, Candi Dieng, Candi Ngempon,dsb dan letaknya memang tersebar di wilayah eks Residen Semarang, Kedu, Banyumas dan Solo. #kilasdokumenter #literasyikgalih @galih.wib
textTranslated: Finally we found another part of the sengi temple complex. Asu Sengi Temple is located in the middle of rice fields. The village road between Magelang continues towards Boyolali via a small bridge. Asu Temple is located in Candipos Hamlet, Sengi Village, Dukun District, Magelang Regency, Central Java. Unfortunately the fence is padlocked, so you can't see inside. The name Asu (dog: Javanese) by local residents is because there is a statue of a Nandi bull that looks like an Asu. It was built in the 9th century during the reign of Kayuwangi Dyah Lokapala from the Hindu Mataram Kingdom. Based on the Sri Manggala II, Kurambitan I and Kurambitan II inscriptions, it is stated that there is a Dharma Salingsingan which was built in 802 Caka.  Similar and almost contemporary with other Hindu Mataram temples such as Gedongsongo Temple, Dieng Temple, Ngempon Temple, etc. and they are located in the former Residential areas of Semarang, Kedu, Banyumas and Solo. #kilasdocumenter #literasyikgalih @galih.wib
title: Asu Temple

address: Q332+3X, Pringapus, Ngadirejo, Pringapus, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: Achmad Noer Cholis
text:
Candi Pringapus terletak di Desa Pringapus, Ngadirejo, Temanggung, berada di lereng sebelah timur Gunung Sindoro. Pada tahun 1844 untuk pertama kalinya Candi Pringapus dicatat oleh F.W Junghun & pada tahun 1929 pemerintah Hindia Belanda memugar candi itu dibawah tanggung jawab Dinas Purbakala (Oudhenkundige Dienst).
.
Diperkirakan Candi Pringapus dibangun pada abad ke 8 - 9 M.
Candi Pringapus terdiri atas 3 bagian berupa Kaki, badan & atap candi.
.
Bagian Kaki candi biasa disebut Bhurloka yang menyimbolkan dunia bawah, tempat orang berdosa.
.
Bagian badan candi disebut Buwarloka yang menyimbolkan dunia tengah, tempat orang² suci yang terbebas dari dosa.
.
Dan bagian atas candi biasa disebut Swarloka, simbol dari alam atas yang dihuni para dewa.
Namun bagian atapnya sudah tidak utuh karena semestinya ada satu puncak lagi sehingga menggambarkan triloka, yakni tiga alam yang dikuasai para dewa.
.
textTranslated:
Pringapus Temple is located in Pringapus Village, Ngadirejo, Temanggung, on the eastern slopes of Mount Sindoro. In 1844, Pringapus Temple was recorded for the first time by F.W Junghun & in 1929 the Dutch East Indies government restored the temple under the responsibility of the Antiquities Service (Oudhenkundige Dienst).
.
It is estimated that Pringapus Temple was built in the 8th - 9th century AD.
Pringapus Temple consists of 3 parts, namely the legs, body & roof of the temple.
.
The foot of the temple is usually called Bhurloka which symbolizes the underworld, the place of sinners.
.
The body of the temple is called Buwarloka which symbolizes the middle world, the place of holy people who are free from sin.
.
And the top of the temple is usually called Swarloka, a symbol of the upper realm inhabited by the gods.
However, the roof is not complete because there should be one more peak so that it represents the triloka, namely the three realms controlled by the gods.
.
title: Pringapus Temple

name: Adhyaksa Putra
text:
Info Arkeologi

Candi Asu terletak di tengah-tengah lahan pertanian masyarakat dan dikelilingi oleh pagar alam yg berupa tanaman yang tertata rapi. Candi Asu berbentuk bujur sangkar dengan ukuran 7,94 meter. Bangunan Candi Asu saat ini tersusun bagian kaki dan tubuhnya, sedangkan atap candi sudah tidak terlihat lagi karena telah runtuh.

Pada bagian kakinya yang memiliki ukuran 2,5 meter terdapat tangga naik ke badan candi. di tanggan itu terdapat Makara yang belum selesai dipahat serta pada pipi tangga pun tidak ada relief yang dipahatkan. Sementara itu, di beberapa dinding kaki candi terdapat ukiran ornamen sulur-suluran yang dibingkai atau biasa disebut dengan hiasan "kertas tempel". Pada bagian tubuh Candi Asu tidak banyak yang tersisa karena sebagian badan polar untuk hingga bagian atap. Namun, masih dapat diperhatikan antefiks yang ada di sekeliling tepi tubuhnya yang tidak terukir hiasan serta enam buah panil yang belum terpahat. Bagian tubuh yang berdiri diatas kakinya lebih kecil bentuknya sehingga terdapat selasar dengan lebar 69 cm. Tubuh Candi Asu bagian bawah terdapat batur yang berbentuk bujur sangkar, pelipit, dan panil. Pada tubuhnya juga terlihat bentuk bekas relung sudah tidak utuh lagi kecuali di sisi utara dengan ukuran 140 cm tingginya dan lebarnya 52 cm. Sementara itu, pada bagian dalam candi terdapat sumuran dengan ukuran panjang 1,31 meter, lebar 1,31 meter, dan kedalaman 4 meter. Bandingkan dengan tubuh Candi Asu yang memiliki ketinggian 3,35 meter.

Di Candi Asu ini ditemukan Arca Nandi yang sudah aus bentuknya sehingga dapat dikatakan bernafaskan agama Hindu. Candi Asu biasanya dikenal juga dengan nama Candi Asu Sengi oleh masyarakat sekitar. penamaan Candi Asu diberikan oleh masyarakat sekitar karena Arca Nandi yang aus tersebut terlihat seperti anjing dalam bahasa Jawa asu. Namun, ada yang berpendapat nama Asu juga berasal bahasa Jawa dari kata ngaso yang berarti istirahat.
textTranslated:
Archaeological Info

Asu Temple is located in the middle of community agricultural land and is surrounded by a natural fence consisting of neatly arranged plants. Asu Temple is square in shape with a size of 7.94 meters. The Asu Temple building currently consists of its legs and body, while the roof of the temple is no longer visible because it has collapsed.

At its foot, which measures 2.5 meters, there are stairs going up to the body of the temple. On the steps there is a Makara that has not been carved yet and there are no reliefs carved on the cheeks of the stairs. Meanwhile, on several walls at the foot of the temple there are ornamental carvings of tendrils which are framed or what is usually called "paste paper" decoration. Not much remains of the body of Asu Temple because part of the body is polar to reach the roof. However, you can still see the antefixes around the edges of the body that are not carved with decoration and six panels that have not been carved. The part of the body that stands on its legs is smaller in shape so that there is a hallway with a width of 69 cm. The lower part of the body of Asu Temple contains square, seam and panel shaped stones. On the body you can also see that the shape of the niche is no longer intact except on the north side with a size of 140 cm in height and 52 cm in width. Meanwhile, inside the temple there is a well with a length of 1.31 meters, a width of 1.31 meters and a depth of 4 meters. Compare this with the body of Asu Temple which has a height of 3.35 meters.

At Asu Temple, a Nandi statue was found whose shape was worn so it could be said to have the breath of Hinduism. Asu Temple is usually also known as Asu Sengi Temple by the local community. The name Asu Temple was given by the local community because the worn Nandi statue looks like a dog in Javanese asu. However, there are those who think that the name Asu also comes from the Javanese word ngaso which means rest.
title: Asu Temple

address: Q332+3X, Pringapus, Ngadirejo, Pringapus, Kec. Ngadirejo, Kabupaten Temanggung, Jawa Tengah 56255, Indonesia
name: Dodi Dodi
text:
Candi Perot berada di lereng sebelah timur Gunung Sindoro yang mempunyai ketinggian 979,40 m di atas permukaan laut. Lokasi candi yang terletak 250 m sebelah barat Candi Pringapus ini, mudah dicapai karena terletak di tengah perkampungan penduduk. Candi Perot mulai dikenal ketika pada tahun 1956, J. G. Casparis menerbitkan prasasti yang ditemukan pada tahun 1819 di dekat candi tersebut. Prasasti yang terbuat dari batu itu bernama Prasasti Tulang Air I yang berukuran 58 x 1 10 cm, dan Prasasti Tulang Air II yang berukuran 59 x 111 cm. Di dalam prasasti yang dikeluarkan pada tanggal 2, bulan Asada Paroterang, hari Aditya Pahing, Tunglai tahun 772 Saka atau 15 Juni 850 M, bertepatan dengan masa pemerintahan Kerajaan Mataram Kuno. Prasasti itu menyebutkan gelar "ratu" bagi Rakai Pikatan yang memerintah di daerah tersebut, dan daftar penguasa yang berkuasa pada waktu itu. Prasasti itu juga menyebutkan bahwa Desa Tulang Air sebagai tempat ditemukannya prasasti tersebut, kemudian ditetapkan sebagai desa perdikan (desa yang bebas dari pajak).
Dokumentasi mengenai Candi Perot sampai sekarang ini tidak lengkap, karena sudah mengalami keruntuhan total. Foto Candi Perot hanya terdapat di Suaka Peninggalan Sejarah dan Purbakala, Jawa Tengah, tetapi tidak disebutkan angka tahun pemotretannya, namun diperkirakan foto tersebut dibuat pada tahun 1920-an. Di dalam foto terlihat candi agak runtuh dan terlilit akar pohon beringin, dan beberapa saat kemudian pohon beringin itu tumbang, sehingga Candi Perot mengalami keruntuhan total. Oleh penduduk setempat reruntuhan batu candi diambil dan dikumpulkan menjadi satu di Kompleks Candi Pringapus, dan beberapa batu candi dimanfaatkan oleh masyarakat sekitar untuk pondasi bangunan rumah, sedangkan beberapa buah batu yang besar masih berada di lokasi yang telah berubah menjadi kebun tembakau, dan sekarang ini menjadi rerumpunan bambu. Setelah dilakukan ekskavasi oleh pihak Suaka Peninggalan Sejarah dan Purbakala, akhirnya berhasil menemukan sisa-sisa bangunan candi, yaitu berupa struktur susunan batu gundul yang mempunyai pola persegi empat dan pondasi bangunan candi yang masih intak. Berdasarkan dari hasil ekskavasi ini diperkirakan bahwa bangunan Candi Perot memiliki denah persegi empat dengan ukuran 6 x 6 m, dan berada pada posisi miring 30° kearah barat daya.

(Renville Siagian, Candi Sebagai Warisan Seni Budaya Indonesia, Yayasan Cempaka Kencana, Yogyakarta, 2002, hal. 52)
textTranslated:
Perot Temple is on the eastern slope of Mount Sindoro which has a height of 979.40 m above sea level. The location of the temple, which is located 250 m west of Pringapus Temple, is easy to reach because it is located in the middle of a residential village. Perot Temple became known when in 1956, J. G. Casparis published an inscription found in 1819 near the temple. The inscriptions made of stone are called the Tulang Air Inscription I, measuring 58 x 110 cm, and the Tulang Air Inscription II, measuring 59 x 111 cm. In the inscription issued on the 2nd of the Asada Paroterang month, Aditya Pahing's day, Tunglai in 772 Saka or June 15, 850 AD, coincides with the reign of the Ancient Mataram Kingdom. The inscription mentions the title "queen" for Rakai Pikatan who ruled in the area, and a list of rulers in power at that time. The inscription also states that Tulang Air Village, where the inscription was found, was then designated as a perdikan village (a village free from taxes).
Documentation regarding Perot Temple is currently incomplete, because it has experienced total collapse. The photo of Perot Temple is only available in the Historical and Archaeological Heritage Sanctuary, Central Java, but the year of the photograph is not stated, but it is estimated that the photo was taken in the 1920s. In the photo, the temple can be seen somewhat collapsed and entangled in the roots of a banyan tree, and a few moments later the banyan tree fell, causing the Perot Temple to completely collapse. By local residents, the ruins of the temple stones were taken and gathered together in the Pringapus Temple Complex, and some of the temple stones were used by the local community for the foundation of house buildings, while several large stones are still in the location which has been turned into a tobacco plantation, and is now a bamboo grove. After excavations were carried out by the Historical and Antiquities Asylum, they finally managed to find the remains of the temple building, namely a bare stone structure with a rectangular pattern and the foundation of the temple building which was still intact. Based on the results of this excavation, it is estimated that the Perot Temple building has a rectangular plan with dimensions of 6 x 6 m, and is tilted at 30° to the southwest.

(Renville Siagian, Temples as Indonesian Cultural Arts Heritage, Cempaka Kencana Foundation, Yogyakarta, 2002, p. 52)
title: Pringapus Temple

name: Dodi Dodi
text:
Sejak zaman Belanda, bangunan candi ini telah menarik perhatian para peneliti untuk mengkaji arsitekturnya. Seperti Van Erp dan Brandes yang menggolongkan arsitektur Candi Asu termasuk periode gaya Jawa Tengah. Ketika candi ini ditemukan, candi Asu telah runtuh akibat bencana gunung Merapi. Candi Asu menghadap ke barat, berbentuk bujur sangkar dan berukuran 7,49 m x 7,49 m, tinggi 2,50 m dan terbuat dari batu andesit.  Salah satu tinggi badan candi yang masih utuh  adalah 3,55 m. Bagian atap candi sudah lama runtuh, sedangkan batu penyusunnya sudah banyak yang hilang sehingga tidak dapat direkonstruksi kembali. Bagian kaki candi yang masih utuh didirikan di atas sebuah batur yang terletak di atas selapis batu yang alasnya berbentuk bujur sangkar. Pintu masuk yang berada di sebelah barat disangga oleh batur sehingga sisi depannya menonjol. Tangga masuk ke candi terdiri atas sembilan anak tangga dengan ukuran lebar 87 m dan di apit oleh pipi tangga setebal 35 cm. Di pipi tangga tidak terdapat hiasan dan sebagian besar batu penyusun pipi tangga telah hilang.
Tubuh candi yang berdiri di atas kaki candi berukuran lebih kecil dari pada kaki candi, sehingga terdapat selasar dengan lebar 69 cm. Secara umum bagian tubuh candi dapat dibagi menjadi tiga bagian yaitu bawah, tengah, dan atas. Tubuh candi bagian bawah terdapat batur yang berbentuk bujur sangkar, pelipit, dan panel. Di setiap sisinya terdapat enam panel yang dipisahkan oleh penyekat yang berjumlah empat buah, tetapi sekarang tinggal dua buah karena sebagian tubuh candi telah runtuh. Di bagian tenggara tubuh candi terdapat bagian yang menonjol, bila kita perhatikan seksama tampak bahwa bagian tersebut belum selesai dikerjakan. Bagian tengah tubuh candi terdapat bingkai setengah lingkaran, yang bagian tepinya dibatasi oleh bidang pilaster yang mengapit relung. Jumlah bidang pilaster ini ada empat buah, yaitu dua buah di sudut dan dua buah mengapit relung. Jumlah relung di bagian tengah tubuh candi ada lima buah, yaitu dua di sisi depan, satu di utara, timur, dan selatan. Relung di utara diapit oleh kala makara yang pahatannya belum selesai, sedangkan relung timur dan selatan hanya terlihat pahatan makara saja. Dari kelima relung yang ada, hanya relung utara yang masih utuh, sedangkan lainnya telah runtuh. Ukuran relung utara yang masih utuh adalah 140 cm untuk tingginya, lebar 52 cm, dan dalamnya 53 cm. Mulai dari tubuh candi bagian atas hingga atap candi tidak diketahui secara pasti bagaimanakah bentuknya, karena telah runtuh dan sebagian besar batu penyusunnya telah hilang. Candi ini memiliki bilik yang ukuran panjangnya 3 m, lebar 2,95 m, dan tinggi yang tersisa 2,33 m. Dari hasil penelitian telah ditemukan sumuran candi di tengah - tengah bilik, berukuran panjang 1,31 m, lebar 1,31 m, dan dalam 4 m. Bagian yang menarik dari Candi Asu adalah banyaknya hiasan candi yang belum sempurna pengerjaannya, sehingga kemungkinan Candi Asu ini belum sampai selesai dalam  pembangunannya sudah runtuh terlebih dahulu karena bencana Gunung Merapi, dan kemudian ditinggalkan oleh  para pemakainya.
(Renville Siagian, Candi Sebagai Warisan Seni Budaya Indonesia, Yayasan Cempaka Kencana, Yogyakarta, 2002, hal. 49-50)
textTranslated:
Since the Dutch era, this temple building has attracted the attention of researchers to study its architecture. Like Van Erp and Brandes who classify the architecture of Asu Temple as belonging to the Central Javanese style period. When this temple was discovered, the Asu temple had collapsed due to the Mount Merapi disaster. Asu Temple faces west, is square and measures 7.49 m x 7.49 m, 2.50 m high and made of andesite stone.  One of the heights of the temple that is still intact is 3.55 m. The roof of the temple had long collapsed, while many of the stones that made it up were missing so it could not be reconstructed. The part of the foot of the temple that is still intact was built on a shelf which is located on a layer of stone whose base is square. The entrance to the west is supported by a stone wall so that the front side stands out. The stairs to enter the temple consist of nine steps with a width of 87 m and are flanked by stairs 35 cm thick. There are no decorations on the stairs and most of the stones that make up the stairs are missing.
The body of the temple that stands at the foot of the temple is smaller than the foot of the temple, so there is a hallway with a width of 69 cm. In general, the body of the temple can be divided into three parts, namely lower, middle and upper. The lower part of the temple body contains square shaped stones, seams and panels. On each side there are six panels separated by four partitions, but now there are only two left because part of the temple has collapsed. In the southeastern part of the temple body there is a protruding part, if we look closely it appears that this part has not been completed. In the center of the temple there is a semi-circular frame, the edges of which are limited by pilasters flanking the niche. There are four pilasters in total, namely two in the corners and two flanking the niche. There are five niches in the center of the temple, namely two on the front side, one on the north, east and south. The niche in the north is flanked by kala makara whose carvings have not been completed, while the eastern and southern niches only have makara carvings visible. Of the five existing niches, only the northern niche is still intact, while the others have collapsed. The size of the northern niche which is still intact is 140 cm in height, 52 cm in width and 53 cm in depth. Starting from the upper body of the temple to the roof of the temple, it is not known exactly how it looks, because it has collapsed and most of the stones that make it up have been lost. This temple has a chamber measuring 3 m in length, 2.95 m in width, and a remaining height of 2.33 m. From the research results, a temple well was found in the middle of the chamber, measuring 1.31 m long, 1.31 m wide and 4 m deep. The interesting part of Asu Temple is that many of the temple decorations have not been completed yet, so it is possible that Asu Temple has not yet completed its construction, it first collapsed due to the Mount Merapi disaster, and was then abandoned by its users.
(Renville Siagian, Temples as Indonesian Cultural Arts Heritage, Cempaka Kencana Foundation, Yogyakarta, 2002, pp. 49-50)
title: Asu Temple

text:
Menurut cerita orang - orang sepuh, konon namanya Candi Aso (Aso = Rehat, Ngaso = Istirahat). Situs yang digunakan oleh pemuka agama hindu yang dulunya digunakan untuk beristirahat para pemuka agama dan pembesar kerajaan hindu semasa itu. Entah apa yang membuat saat ini lebih dikenal dengan Candi Asu (Asu = Anjing) yang konotasinya dalam bahasa termasuk ungkapan yang lebih mengacu kepada umpatan atau kata - kata kotor bagi mayoritas orang Jawa.
Kebetulan rumah saya tidak jauh dari tempat itu dan isteriku orang situ.
textTranslated:
According to the stories of elderly people, it is said that the name is Aso Temple (Aso = rest, Ngaso = rest). The site used by Hindu religious leaders was previously used to rest for religious leaders and dignitaries of the Hindu kingdom at that time. I don't know what makes it now better known as Candi Asu (Asu = Dog) whose connotation in the language includes expressions that refer more to curses or dirty words for the majority of Javanese people.
Coincidentally, my house is not far from that place and my wife is from there.
title: Asu Temple

name: Poerdjianto Bambang
text: Terletak 3 km dari pusat kota Muntilan, dengan jalan aspal cukup bagus dng kondisi jalan menurun terus sampai candi. Posisi dipinggir pertigaan jalan desa, mudah dijangkau cm tdk ada lahan parkir jd parkirnya di bahu jalan yg agak sempit. Candinya cukup bagus sbg tempat pembelajaran sejarah bagi kita semua, krn blom buka (blom jam buka) jd kemarin cm foto dari luar pagar.
textTranslated: Located 3 km from the center of Muntilan city, the asphalt road is quite good and the road continues downhill to the temple. Position on the edge of a village road junction, easy to reach but there is no parking space so parking is on the shoulder of a rather narrow road. The temple is quite good as a place to learn history for all of us, because it's not open yet (not opening hours) so yesterday we took photos from outside the fence.
title: Ngawen Temple

address: 97WC+8XC, Unnamed Road, Ngawen, Kec. Muntilan, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56415, Indonesia
name: Ulyn Yumna
text:
Salah satu cagar budaya peninggalan sejarah yang patut dilestarikan meskipun keberadaannya tidak se-Wow candi lainnya di wilayah Muntilan.
Area candinya terbilang kecil namun jejak sejarah sangat kental.
Terbukti dengan adanya 1 bangunan candi utuh ditambah candi-candi lain yang masih terus berproses untuk dipugar kembali.
Untuk areanya sangat terawat.
Area parkir motor bisa di bahu jalan.
textTranslated:
One of the historical cultural heritage sites that is worth preserving even though its existence is not as impressive as other temples in the Muntilan area.
The temple area is relatively small but traces of history are very strong.
This is proven by the existence of 1 intact temple building plus other temples which are still in the process of being restored.
The area is very well maintained.
The motorbike parking area can be on the shoulder of the road.
title: Ngawen Temple

address: 97WC+8XC, Unnamed Road, Ngawen, Kec. Muntilan, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56415, Indonesia
name: Lusia W (Lusweek)
text: Lokasi sangat mudah dijangkau. Tidak ada tiket masuk alias gratis, hanya mengisi buku daftar pengunjung.
textTranslated: The location is very easy to reach. There is no entrance ticket or free, just fill in the visitor register book.
title: Ngawen Temple

address: 97WC+8XC, Unnamed Road, Ngawen, Kec. Muntilan, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56415, Indonesia

text: Dekat rumah. Tenang, sejuk dan murah meriah karena gratis alias tanpa tiket masuk. Sekitarnya ada warung koq. Tenang saja!!
textTranslated: Near home. Calm, cool and cheap because it's free, aka no entrance ticket. There are koq stalls nearby. Stay cool!!
title: Ngawen Temple

address: 97WC+8XC, Unnamed Road, Ngawen, Kec. Muntilan, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56415, Indonesia
name: Keperluan Penelitian
text:
Candi Ngawen merupakan candi Buddha. Ada 5 buah candi yang berjejer dan hanya 1 candi yang utuh, sisanya hanya meninggalkan kaki candi.

Akses ke tempat ini mudah karena berada dipinggir jalan. Tidak ada tiket masuk ke candi hanya cukupelapor ke petugas dan mengisi buku tamu. Ada toilet di pos penjaga. Yang unik dari kompleks candi ngawen disedikannya perpustakaan mini bagi yang ingin mengetahui sejarah dam proses pembuatan candi. Disekitar candi juga terdapat tempat makan. Hanya saja tempat parkir cukup sulit sehingga harus parkir di bahu jalan.

Candi buka pukul 08:00 - 16:00. Petugasnya sangat ramah.
textTranslated:
Ngawen Temple is a Buddhist temple. There are 5 temples in a row and only 1 temple is intact, the rest only leaves the foot of the temple.

Access to this place is easy because it is located on the side of the road. There is no entrance ticket to the temple, just report to the officer and fill in the guest book. There is a toilet at the guard post. What is unique about the Ngawen temple complex is that it provides a mini library for those who want to know the history and process of making the temple. Around the temple there are also places to eat. It's just that parking is quite difficult so you have to park on the shoulder of the road.

The temple is open 08:00 - 16:00. The officers are very friendly.
title: Ngawen Temple

address: 97WC+8XC, Unnamed Road, Ngawen, Kec. Muntilan, Kabupaten Magelang, Jawa Tengah 56415, Indonesia
name: galih akademik
text:
Candi Ngawen terletak di Muntilan Kab Magelang. Dari jalan raya masuk kampung sekitar 1 km arah sendangsono. Candi Ngawen ini sudah dipugar dan dijaga oleh pegawai @bpcbjateng . Gratis dan sayangnya terletak tepat di persimpangan jalan jadi susah untuk parkir. Diperkirakan dibangun abad VIII di masa syailendra merupakan Dyani Budha. temuan arca Dhyani Buddha Ratnasambhawa di Candi II dan arca Dhyani Buddha Amithaba di Candi IV sebagai bukti, tapi beberapa kepala arca hilang. Terdiri dari 5 bangunan candi. Hanya candi II yang lengkap. Batu seputar candi belum bisa disusun kembali sejak eskavasi Van Erp 1920. Uniknya pada candi II dan Candi IV terdapat ukiran arca singa di keempat sudutnya, yang mirip bangunan candi di Kamboja maupun Khmer. Prasasti yang terpahat ada kala makara, kinara kinari dan pohon kalpataru. Menurut soekmono candi ini merupakan venuvana sesuai prasasti Karangtengah. Jika kebanyakan Candi Buddha menghadap ke arah Barat, Candi Ngawen ini justru menghadap ke arah Timur yang menjadi ciri Candi Hindu. Dengan demikian, bisa dibilang, candi dengan luas sekitar 3.373 meter persegi ini merupakan akulturasi dua agama. Antara Buddha dan Hindu.
#literasyikgalih #kilasdokumenter
textTranslated:
Ngawen Temple is located in Muntilan, Magelang Regency. From the main road you enter the village about 1 km towards Sendangsono. Ngawen Temple has been restored and is guarded by @bpcbjateng employees. It's free and unfortunately it's located right at a crossroads so it's hard to park. It is estimated that it was built in the VIII century during the Syailendra era, namely Dyani Buddha. the discovery of the Dhyani Buddha Ratnasambhawa statue in Temple II and the Dhyani Buddha Amithaba statue in Temple IV as evidence, but several statue heads were missing. Consists of 5 temple buildings. Only temple II is complete. The stones around the temple have not been able to be reassembled since the Van Erp excavations in 1920. What is unique about Temple II and IV are carved lion statues in the four corners, which is similar to temple buildings in Cambodia and Khmer. The inscriptions carved include kala makara, kinara kinari and kalpataru tree. According to Soekmono, this temple is a venuvana according to the Karangtengah inscription. If most Buddhist temples face west, Ngawen temple faces east, which is characteristic of Hindu temples. Thus, you could say, this temple with an area of ​​around 3,373 square meters is an acculturation of two religions. Between Buddhism and Hinduism.
#literaturesyikgalih #documentaryflash

text:
Saya tidak pernah menolak jika diajak mengunjungi candi, candi apapun itu, Buddhis maupun Siwa.  Kali ini mengunjungi candi Ngawen, yang jika dilihat dari peta, posisi candi ini dapat ditarik dengan garis lurus dengan 3 candi yaitu Mendut, Pawon dan Borobudur.

Letaknya tidak jauh dari Mendut, di saat pandemi ini masih tertutup untuk umum tetapi masuk dengan meminta izin ke BPCB Jateng secara online. Mudah kok, demi kebaikan bersama mari ikuti prosedur ya..

Candi ini terdapat 5 Candi dengan kondisi nyaris utuh hanya 1 candi dgn ciri khas Singa menerkam di 4 sudut, itu pun minus bagian atas, 3 reruntuhan candi, 1 tapak candi dengan buddharupang vara mudra tanpa kepala.  Hanya terlihat 2 Buddharupang, 1 lagi berada di dalam candi yang nyaris utuh itu.

Kami melakukan penghormatan dengan membaca paritta singkat dan bermeditasi . Kali ini saya menggunakan kostum Jawa walau tidak lengkap karena menurut beberapa sesepuh jika demikian, para penjaga Candi sangat senang dengan kehadiran kita.  Dan benar saja, saya mendapat informasi tambahan yang selama ini tidak tahu sama sekali, sebenarnya di candi ini terdapat sumber air yang sudah saya tanyakan sejak dulu, bukannya seharusnya candi dibangun di dekat sumber air, yang digunakan sebagai tempat membersihkan dan penyucian diri sebelum puja dan ziarah.

Informasi kedua adalah terdapat 6 situs sekitar kawasan Borobudur, dimana 5 diantaranya adalah candi Siwa yang terbukti dengan adanya Lingga Yoni.

Hmmm, mungkin seharusnya seragam kostum Jawa diajukan sebagai alternatif kostum mengunjungi Candi Jawa, selain lebih sopan juga lebih dapat meresapi kearifan lokal yang ada.

Mari kunjungi, pelajari, cintai, lindungi warisan mahakarya leluhur nusantara..

Demikianlah kura-kura.. ohya, yoni di kawasan ini unik lho,  beralas kura-kura dan garuda.

#candingawen
textTranslated:
I never refuse to be invited to visit a temple, any temple, Buddhist or Shiva.  This time we visited Ngawen temple, which if you look at the map, the position of this temple can be drawn in a straight line with 3 temples, namely Mendut, Pawon and Borobudur.

It is located not far from Mendut, during the pandemic it is still closed to the public but entry can be done by requesting permission from the Central Java BPCB online. It's easy, for the common good, let's follow the procedure.

This temple has 5 temples in almost intact condition, only 1 temple with the characteristic of a lion pouncing in 4 corners, that's minus the top, 3 temple ruins, 1 temple site with a headless buddharupang vara mudra.  You can only see 2 Buddharupangs, 1 more is in the temple which is almost intact.

We pay our respects by reciting a short chant and meditating. This time I wore a Javanese costume even though it was incomplete because according to some of the elders, the temple guards were very happy with our presence.  And sure enough, I got additional information that I didn't know at all, actually in this temple there is a water source which I have been asking about for a long time, instead the temple should be built near a water source, which is used as a place to clean and purify oneself before puja and pilgrimage.

The second piece of information is that there are 6 sites around the Borobudur area, of which 5 are Shiva temples which are proven by the existence of the Lingga Yoni.

Hmmm, maybe a Javanese costume uniform should be proposed as an alternative costume for visiting Javanese temples, apart from being more polite it also allows you to better absorb existing local wisdom.

Come visit, learn, love, protect the legacy of the archipelago's ancestral masterpieces...

That's the turtle... oh yes, the yoni in this area is unique, you know, based on a turtle and an eagle.

text:
Candi Ngawen merupakan kompleks percandian yang berada di Desa Ngawen, Muntilan, Magelang. Pertama kali dilaporkan oleh N. W Hoepermans pada tahun 1864.
.
Kompleks candi ini memiliki 5 bangunan candi namun hanya ada satu bangunan candi yang masih utuh, yang lainnya hanya tersisa reruntuhan & bagian kaki candi saja.
.
Candi Ngawen merupakan Candi Buddha namun sekilas bentuk bangunannya seperti candi Hindu, diperkirakan dibangun pada periode 812 – 836 Masehi menurut para sejarawan.
.
Terdapat juga arca Dhyani Buddha Ratnasambhawa di Candi II & arca Dhyani Buddha Amithaba di Candi IV, walaupun kondisinya sudah tidak utuh. .
Salah satu daya tarik & keunikan candi ini adalah adanya arca singa disetiap sudut kaki candi, terdapat juga makara ditangga candi, kala kirtimuka, relief Gana, sulur – suluran tumbuhan dan lain sebagainya.
textTranslated:
Ngawen Temple is a temple complex located in Ngawen Village, Muntilan, Magelang. First reported by N. W Hoepermans in 1864.
.
This temple complex has 5 temple buildings, but only one temple building is still intact, the rest are only ruins & the foot of the temple.
.
Ngawen Temple is a Buddhist temple, but at first glance the building looks like a Hindu temple, it is estimated that it was built in the period 812 – 836 AD according to historians.
.
There is also a statue of Dhyani Buddha Ratnasambhawa in Temple II & a statue of Dhyani Buddha Amithaba in Temple IV, although their condition is not intact. .
One of the attractions & uniqueness of this temple is the presence of lion statues at every corner of the foot of the temple, there are also makara on the steps of the temple, kala kirtimuka, Gana reliefs, plant tendrils and so on.
title: Ngawen Temple

text:
Candi ini terdiri dari lima bangunan candi yang berukuran kecil, dua di antaranya mempunyai bentuk yang berbeda dengan dihiasi oleh patung singa pada keempat sudutnya. Sebentuk patung Buddha yang sudah tidak berkepala dengan posisi duduk Ratnasambawa tampak berada pada salah satu candi lainnya. Beberapa relief pada sisi candi masih tampak cukup jelas, di antaranya adalah ukiran Kinnara, Kinnari, dan kala-makara. Posisi hiasan Kinnara Kinnari mengapit Kalpataru. Kinnara dan Kinnari menggambarkan mahkluk kahyangan yang berwujud setengah manusia dan setengah burung. Sementara itu, Kalpataru merupakan pohon kahyangan yang hidup sepanjang masa tempat dimana menggantungkan segala asa. Pohon ini digambarkan memiliki dahan-dahan yang diartikan sebagai untaian perhiasan yang indah, sehingga dijaga makhluk-makhluk kahyangan seperti Kinara Kinari.

Untuk masuk di candi ngawen cukup mengisi buku tamu.
Karena sepi pengunjung bisa berbincang bincang sama petugas
textTranslated:
This temple consists of five small temple buildings, two of which have different shapes and are decorated with lion statues on the four corners. A headless Buddha statue in Ratnasambawa's sitting position appears in one of the other temples. Some of the reliefs on the side of the temple are still quite clear, including carvings of Kinnara, Kinnari and kala-makara. The position of the Kinnara Kinnari decoration flanks Kalpataru. Kinnara and Kinnari describe heavenly creatures who are half human and half bird. Meanwhile, Kalpataru is a heavenly tree that lives throughout time, a place where all hopes depend. This tree is described as having branches which are interpreted as strands of beautiful jewelry, so it is guarded by heavenly creatures such as Kinara Kinari.

To enter Ngawen temple, just fill in the guest book.
Because it was quiet, visitors could chat with the officers
title: Ngawen Temple
